{% extends 'email.html.twig' %}


{% block title %}Introducing Purchases + Promos{% endblock title %}

{% block content %}
    Hey there! <br><br>

    One of the most commonly requested features has been to be able to track your bike related purchases - and now you can!
    <br>
    <br>
    <img src="{{ website ~ asset('images/app/images/purchases.png') }}" alt="Purchases" style="display: block; margin: 0 auto; width:282px; max-width: 100%; border: none;">
    <br>
    Now you can track how much you spend on maintenance of your bike as well as new parts or even paying off a new bike!
    Also coming soon is a new dashboard with a balance chart. Stay tuned.
    <br><br>
    There's also a new <a href="{{ website ~ path('reward.promo.list') }}" style="color: #333333;">Promos section</a> on PiggyBike where I
    list promos and coupon codes from <a href="{{ pushys_url }}" style="color: #333333;">Pushys.com.au</a>. I've been a longtime customer of Pushys
    as they've consistently delivered super quickly in Brisbane and have really good prices.
    <br><br>

    <!-- BULLETPROOF BUTTON -->
    <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="mobile-button-container">
        <tr>
            <td align="center" style="padding: 25px 0 0 0;" class="padding-copy">
                <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="responsive-table">
                    <tr>
                        <td align="center">
                            <a href="{{ website ~ path('reward.reward.list') }}" target="_blank" style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; color: #ffffff; text-decoration: none; background-color: #256F9C; border-top: 15px solid #256F9C; border-bottom: 15px solid #256F9C; border-left: 25px solid #256F9C; border-right: 25px solid #256F9C; border-radius: 3px; -webkit-border-radius: 3px; -moz-border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block;" class="mobile-button">
                                Check out the new features</a>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>
    <br>
    <br>
    As always, if you have any feedback, I'm keen to hear it.
    <br>
    <br>

    Happy Riding, <br>
    Tom

{% endblock content %}

